        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 4:54PM MDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 454 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms 7 miles southeast of Rhame, or 8 miles west of Bowman,
moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bowman, Rhame, Mud Buttes, Griffin, Sunset Butte, and Bowman Haley
Dam.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
